<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="557" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-02-02"><hi rend="italic">February 2,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 722.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Robert J. Thompson, of Chicago, who is
                            secretary of the Lafayette Memorial Commission, has been appointed by
                            the President a special commissioner to present to the President of the
                            French Republic the first Lafayette coin of a series of $50,000
                            authorized by Congress in aid of the Lafayette memorial statue.</p>
                        <p>The President will be pleased if you will make an appointment with His
                            Excellency President Loubet to present Mr. Thompson and to allow him the
                            privilege of presenting this coin in a silver casket especially designed
                            for the purpose.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>